This is likely to develop into a general war involving several of the Arab states plus Iran. Israel has several hundred nuclear weapons by most accounts. Iraq and Iran might have at least one, and they certainly have poison gas. Ariel Sharon once promised to &quot;sterilize western Iraq with neutron bombs&quot; if the Iraqis used weapons of mass destruction against Israel. The same would presumably go for any other country that uses them against Israel. I really hope that this turns out to be off-topic. If not, it's bye-bye Baghdad.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/uprojectorion.showPublicProfile?language=EN>projectorion</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Nuclear Renaissance Man</span><br>  Posts: 833<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(3/29/02 8:52 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=295.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.fas.org/nuke/hew/Usa/Tests/Rwmohawk2.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://home.earthlink.net/~projectorion/ezboard/posticons/3.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Middle East War</span><hr size=1> I've been telling people for years that a nuclear war is inevitable if we keep following the current path were on. You can't uninvent it and war is a part of human nature. We are no more enlightened than our ancestors. That theory is bunk.<br>
The only thing we have control over is the possible impact and therein lies the only method of breaking the cycle. We take nuclear power out of the limitations we have imposed on it. Weapons and commercial energy production. We colonise space and make nuclear weapons redundant overnight.<br>
An asteroid nudged into the Earth would be equivalent to thousands of nukes. We will be able to police space with an interplanetary military and safely dismantle all Earth based nuclear warheads in the knowledge that any secretly hidden can't be used. The offender would find their nation incinerated by a big rock from space.<br>
In exploring atomic spaceflight we will learn to better understand nuclear power and with understanding comes development of methods to defend against it. An off Earth customs service would easily detect all heavy elements smuggled on ships. Just try and get a radioactive metal like Uranium through metal detectors and Xray machines. Its impossible.   <p>~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
